                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header">
                                <i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                <span class="question__title">
                                    Is Namecheap Shared Server Hosting cloud-based?
                                </span>
                            </div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">
                                No, although all Namecheap Shared Hosting plans are hosted on a
                                Solid-State Drive (SSD), which helps to enhance performance over
                                traditional hard disk drives (HDD). SSDs also contain no moving
                                mechanical parts, offering faster access time and low latency.
                                Namecheap
                                <a href="/hosting/shared/" target="_blank">Stellar Business plans</a>
                                with a US datacenter and all plans with an EU datacenter are,
                                however, based on Cloud Storage. Here, traditional physical
                                machines are converted to virtual machines (VM), running on a
                                readily-available VM infrastructure.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
